item.title: Need Help With Java!
item.dc:creator: @VB7_Rocks VB7 Rocks
item.description:
@VB7_Rocks wrote:

Frell:

The java is creating too many javaobjects and your computer can handle it so its throwing heaps.

You can’t throw heaps -.-

Heap: The area of unallocated memory on a PC, usually RAM. If you can’t reserve enough memory in the heap, it means there isn’t enough memory on the computer to run the Java application.

item.title: Need Help With Java!
item.dc:creator: @VB7_Rocks VB7 Rocks
item.description:
@VB7_Rocks wrote:

Samir LOL:

Then how the hell did the other guy fix it? And my computer didnt fail, its not lik my comptuer is totally crap now, it runs everything else, computers arent ment just for moparscape

Can’t you read?

The error message clearly states that it can’t reserve enough memory for the Java VM, which means you have a really crappy amount of RAM, and therefore, your computer does fail.

The other guy probably ‘fixed’ it by restarting the computer and clearing out just enough memory in the heap for the VM to initialize, but I wouldn’t count on it running for long.
